.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/feature_catalog/04--model-benchmark-mode/03-opt-in-5dim-scorer.md:12:This feature controls how `run-benchmark.cjs` judges materialized outputs. It keeps the deterministic byte-identical scorer as the default and exposes the richer five-dimension scorer behind explicit flags.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/feature_catalog/04--model-benchmark-mode/03-opt-in-5dim-scorer.md:18:`run-benchmark.cjs --scorer pattern` is the default. It uses the byte-identical heading and pattern matcher, so a run with no scorer flag produces the same deterministic result as before. `--scorer 5dim` is opt-in: it routes materialized outputs through `scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/score-model-variant.cjs`, the ported five-dimension scorer that combines deterministic checks with a pluggable grader.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/feature_catalog/04--model-benchmark-mode/03-opt-in-5dim-scorer.md:30:| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/run-benchmark.cjs` | Benchmark runner | Resolves `--scorer` and `--grader`, runs the default pattern matcher, and stamps `scoringMethod` on the report. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/feature_catalog/04--model-benchmark-mode/03-opt-in-5dim-scorer.md:31:| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/score-model-variant.cjs` | 5-dim scorer | Ported five-dimension scorer reached only under `--scorer 5dim`. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/feature_catalog/04--model-benchmark-mode/03-opt-in-5dim-scorer.md:32:| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/harness.cjs` | Grader harness | Hosts the pluggable `noop`, `mock`, and `llm` grader paths the 5-dim scorer consumes. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/feature_catalog/04--model-benchmark-mode/03-opt-in-5dim-scorer.md:38:| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/tests/optin-scorer.vitest.ts` | Automated test | Verifies pattern-default parity, `--scorer 5dim` routing, grader selection, and `scoringMethod` stamping end to end. |
