.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/references/shared/promotion_gate_contract.md:21:Promotion is a narrow, gated operation that moves a packet-local candidate into the canonical target location. The promotion gate contract defines the five required gates that must all pass before mutation is allowed: prompt scoring, benchmark status, repeatability evidence, manifest boundary compliance, and explicit operator approval.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/references/shared/promotion_gate_contract.md:25:**Rollback script:** `scripts/agent-improvement/rollback-candidate.cjs`
