.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/README.md:20:- The public `score()` API takes criteria and an absolute `cwd`, never a fixture file path. The caller passes the criteria as data.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/README.md:21:- It synthesizes an in-memory virtual fixture, writes it to a temp JSON, and runs the deterministic check scripts plus the grader against it, then removes the temp dir.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/README.md:22:- Dimensions: D1 acceptance, D2 bundle gate (hard gate), D3 cwd/path, D4 grader, D5 pre-planning. Weights live in `DEFAULT_RUBRIC`.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/README.md:23:- D2 is the hard gate: when it fails, D1 is capped to 0 and `hard_gate_failed` is set.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/README.md:35:│ score-model-variant  │  builds virtual fixture (absolute cwd)
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/README.md:56:│ apply hard gate -> weighted score over D1..D5         │
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/README.md:73:+-- deterministic/            # D1-style + D2/D3/D5 deterministic check scripts
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/README.md:84:| `score-model-variant.cjs` | Public `score()` orchestration. Synthesizes the virtual fixture, runs each deterministic check via `runDetCheck`, builds the grader via `buildGraderFn`, applies the hard gate, and computes the weighted score. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/README.md:106:| `score({ candidateId, outputText, criteria, cwd, graderKind })` | Function | Returns `{ fixtureId, weightedScore, dimensions, hard_gate_failed, deterministic, grader, interaction_terms }`. |
