.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:1:This release lands the 042 Phase 5 "agent-improver deep-loop alignment" work plus the `sk-agent-improver to deep-agent-improvement` rename. The improver now has its own frozen stop-reason taxonomy, append-only audit journal, mutation coverage graph with trade-off detection, directed candidate run history, and benchmark stability scoring - aligning its runtime truth model with `sk-deep-research` and `sk-deep-review`. The proposal-only agent constraint is preserved: all new journaling happens orchestrator-side, never from the improver itself. The goal is to make the workflow easier to follow and easier to trust.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:5:#### Skill Rename: sk-agent-improver → deep-agent-improvement
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:7:- The skill and its sibling `sk-prompt` were renamed to the verb-first `deep/root` convention used by the other `/deep:*` slash commands.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:9:- The `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` command continues to drive the loop; no operator-facing command changed.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:25:- Added `scripts/trade-off-detector.cjs` - Pareto-aware dimension trade-off detection. When a candidate improves one dimension but regresses another, the detector surfaces the trade-off rather than silently accepting the regression.
