.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/opus/iterations/iteration-005.md:43:### F-5 — `aliases.ts` enables a zero-downtime ALIAS-BRIDGE migration (Q3 RESOLVED — viable)
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/opus/iterations/iteration-005.md:44:`mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts` maps a canonical skill id to alias strings via `RAW_ALIAS_GROUPS` and resolves through `canonicalSkillId()` / `skillMatchesAlias()`. The group `'deep-agent-improvement': ['command-spec-kit-deep-agent-improvement', '/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop', 'deep-agent-improvement', 'sk-deep-agent-improvement']` (lines 27–32) shows it **supports skill-name aliasing** [SOURCE: aliases.ts:5,27-32,59-69]. Therefore the bridge is real: set canonical to `deep-improvement` and **keep `deep-agent-improvement` + `sk-deep-agent-improvement` as aliases** so legacy references and saved continuity keep resolving during/after transition. The `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` command string can also remain an alias even if the command file is not renamed (see F-7).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/opus/iterations/iteration-005.md:45:- **Actionable:** update the canonical key to `deep-improvement`, retain old names as aliases (permanently or until a later cleanup packet) — this is the single highest-leverage move to eliminate the dangling window.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/opus/iterations/iteration-005.md:47:### F-6 — Generated indexes must be rebuilt LAST (ordering invariant), never hand-edited mid-rename
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/opus/iterations/iteration-005.md:49:- `.opencode/specs/descriptions.json:57` (generated by `generate-description.js`; memory-search uses it), per-folder `graph-metadata.json` (backfilled by `generate-context.js`), advisor `skill-graph.json`/`graph-metadata.json` (via `advisor_rebuild`/`skill_graph_scan`), and the code-graph (via `code_graph_scan`) [SOURCE: Grep count, `descriptions.json` row; CLAUDE.md §3 "auto-generated/refreshed by generate-context.js"; session `mcp__mk_skill_advisor__*` + `mcp__mk_code_index__*` tool registry].
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/opus/iterations/iteration-005.md:52:### F-7 — Scope ambiguity: literal skill-id swap vs the wider `agent-improvement` token family
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/opus/iterations/iteration-005.md:53:The literal rename only drops "agent": `deep-agent-improvement → deep-improvement`. But adjacent tokens contain `agent-improvement` WITHOUT the full skill name, so a strict skill-name swap leaves them and creates naming drift:
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/opus/iterations/iteration-005.md:54:- Command `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` (file `.opencode/commands/deep/start-agent-improvement-loop.md:16` + assets `deep_start-agent-improvement-loop_auto.yaml:34` / `_confirm.yaml:36`) [SOURCE: Grep count, command rows].
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/opus/iterations/iteration-005.md:55:- Asset/script subdirs `assets/agent-improvement/` + `scripts/agent-improvement/`, and the loop state file `agent-improvement-state.jsonl` [SOURCE: Glob, `*/agent-improvement/*` + `*/agent-improvement-state.jsonl` paths].
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/opus/iterations/iteration-005.md:57:- **Decision required:** (a) **narrow** — rename only the skill/agent id, leaving `start-agent-improvement-loop`, asset dirs, and state files as-is (lowest blast radius; the advisor alias from F-5 keeps the command string resolving; but inconsistent); or (b) **wide** — also `agent-improvement → improvement` for command, asset/script dirs, and state files (consistent, but larger; touches loop state-file names that resume/continuity readers parse). This is the single biggest scope fork in RQ6.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/opus/iterations/iteration-005.md:67:### F-9 — `test-fixtures/060-stress-test` mirrors are FIXTURES (cp-improve-target), not the skill id — verify before touching
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/opus/iterations/iteration-005.md:68:The stress-test fixture tree contains its own 4-runtime mirror set targeting `cp-improve-target` (a synthetic improvement target), distinct from the skill name: `test-fixtures/060-stress-test/.{opencode,claude,gemini,codex}/agents/cp-improve-target.*` [SOURCE: Glob, `test-fixtures/060-stress-test/*` paths]. Any `deep-agent-improvement` hit there is the skill referring to itself in fixture setup; renaming the *fixture target* would break the stress tests. **Actionable:** content-sweep references to the skill, but do NOT rename `cp-improve-target`; re-run the stress suite after.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/opus/iterations/iteration-005.md:71:Rebuilding indexes triggers the MCP daemon's known behavior of mass-writing 1400+ `graph-metadata.json` files into the working tree (it does not stage/commit). During rebuild this produces large churn. **Actionable:** scope every commit explicitly (never `git add -A`); deliberately commit the rename changeset and the regenerated-index changeset, ignoring unrelated daemon churn [SOURCE: user memory `daemon-index-staging-hazard`; CLAUDE.md startup memory index].
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/opus/iterations/iteration-005.md:76:1. **(Bridge)** In `scorer/aliases.ts`, change the canonical key to `deep-improvement` and KEEP `deep-agent-improvement` + `sk-deep-agent-improvement` + `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` as aliases; commit. Both names resolve.
