.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.4.0.0.md:1:# v1.4.0.0 - Skill Rename: sk-improve-agent to deep-agent-improvement
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.4.0.0.md:7:This changelog records the active skill-family rename from `sk-improve-agent` to `deep-agent-improvement` and the migration boundary for paths, metadata, and runtime references.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.4.0.0.md:11:This release renames the skill from `sk-improve-agent` to `deep-agent-improvement` so the skill folder, skill identity, metadata, and active documentation use the `deep-*` naming convention while preserving the existing agent and command surfaces. Git history around the rename shows the pre-v1.5 family still using `sk-improve-agent` in changelog/docs commits and the later v1.5 packet completing the separate `@improve-agent` agent rename.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.4.0.0.md:15:- Skill folder: `.opencode/skill/sk-improve-agent/` moved to `.opencode/skill/deep-agent-improvement/` in the then-current singular OpenCode layout. The later plural-layout migration moved it again to `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/`.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.4.0.0.md:16:- Skill identity: skill frontmatter, trigger phrases, key files, and derived entities now use `deep-agent-improvement`.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.4.0.0.md:18:- Command surfaces in 4 runtimes: OpenCode/Copilot, Claude, Codex, and Gemini command surfaces keep `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` while routing references move to the new skill path.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.4.0.0.md:19:- Agent skill-matrix lines in 4 runtimes: OpenCode/Copilot, Claude, Codex, and Gemini agent matrices keep the then-current `@improve-agent` identity while pointing at `deep-agent-improvement`; v1.5.0.0 later renames the agent itself.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.4.0.0.md:21:- Install guides: installation and packaging instructions install `deep-agent-improvement`.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.4.0.0.md:25:The old `sk-improve-agent` skill name no longer resolves. Use `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/` for current skill files, references, assets, scripts, feature catalog entries, and manual testing playbooks. The command `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` is unchanged. Agent identity migration is documented separately in v1.5.0.0.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/changelog/v1.4.0.0.md:29:This rename follows the sister rename in `specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/070-sk-deep-rename/`, which moved `sk-deep-review` and `sk-deep-research` to `deep-review` and `deep-research`.
