   181	### RQ7 — External Prior Art
   182	
   183	Mapped so Lane C reuses proven metrics rather than inventing them. **Coverage caveat for model comparison:** DeepSeek and GPT-5.5 had live web access and actually fetched sources; **Opus's web was permission-gated** so all its citations are flagged `[web-unverified]` (drawn from established knowledge, recommended for later confirmation) `[opus/i1 web-note]`; MiniMax cited a mix.
   184	
   185	| Prior art | What transfers to Lane C | Surfaced by |
   186	|---|---|---|
   187	| **BFCL v4** (Berkeley Function Calling) | AST-based correctness; **Irrelevance Detection** = activation precision/abstention; Executor-Relevant = intra-skill routing; latency/cost metrics → D3 | DeepSeek `[deepseek/i1]`, Opus, MiniMax `[SOURCE: gorilla.cs.berkeley.edu/leaderboard.html]` |
   188	| **MetaTool** | tool-usage *awareness* vs tool *selection* split → D1's inter/intra separation; reliability/abstention | GPT-5.5 `[gpt55/i1 f-03]`, Opus `[SOURCE: arxiv.org/abs/2310.03128]` |
   189	| **ToolLLM / ToolBench / ToolEval** | scenario-construction pipeline → fixture gen (RQ4); pass-rate + win-rate → D1 + D4; nDCG retriever eval → D2 | DeepSeek, GPT-5.5, Opus `[SOURCE: arxiv.org/abs/2307.16789]` |
   190	| **MCP-Bench** | fuzzy instructions *without explicit tool names* → hint-free harness; tool-/trajectory-/task-level eval | GPT-5.5 `[gpt55/i1 f-04]` `[SOURCE: arxiv.org/abs/2508.20453]` |
   191	| **Ragas** | context precision/recall, context utilization, tool-call F1, agent goal accuracy → D2/D3 columns | GPT-5.5, Opus `[SOURCE: docs.ragas.io]` |
   192	| **LangSmith** | trajectory eval, run model (inputs/outputs/intermediate steps/feedback), pairwise comparison → D4 ablation, scenarioRows | GPT-5.5 `[gpt55/i1, i4]` |
   193	| **AgentBench / SWE-bench / τ-bench / GAIA / WebArena** | execution-based scoring > final-answer "vibes"; steps/tool-call counts as efficiency metrics → D3 | DeepSeek, GPT-5.5, Opus `[SOURCE: arxiv.org/abs/2308.03688]` |
   194	| **MT-Bench / Chatbot Arena / G-Eval** | LLM-as-judge canon + position/verbosity/self-preference bias mitigations → D4 grader | Opus `[opus/i1 F5]` `[web-unverified]` |
   195	| **Self-RAG** | adaptive-retrieval "was this retrieval necessary?" reflection → D2 "did loading this ref help?" | DeepSeek `[deepseek/i1]` `[SOURCE: arxiv.org/abs/2310.11511]` |
   196	| **Dynabench** | "actionable insights not aggregate accuracy"; human-in-loop loop = run→fix→re-run | DeepSeek `[deepseek/i4 F-RQ5-G]` `[SOURCE: arxiv.org/abs/2104.14337]` |
   197	| **Constitutional AI** | domain-constitution prompt gen (1 degree from triggers) → RQ4 anti-circularity | DeepSeek `[deepseek/i3]` `[SOURCE: arxiv.org/abs/2212.08073]` |
   198	| **APE / Toolformer** | generate instructions from demonstrations not labels; API-call annotation → hint-free fixture gen | DeepSeek `[deepseek/i2]` |
   199	| **BIG-bench canary GUID** | inert marker → "consumed not just opened" + contamination detection | Opus `[opus/i2 F3]` `[web-unverified]` |
   200	| **Metamorphic testing** | semantics-preserving transform + invariance assertion → non-circular T1 fixtures | Opus `[opus/i3 F8]` |
   201	| **Benchmark-leakage research (AAAI)** | public/overfit material inflates capability; private/dynamic test construction | GPT-5.5 `[gpt55/i3]` `[SOURCE: ojs.aaai.org/index.php/AAAI/article/view/41098]` |
   202	| **OpenTelemetry / OpenAI Agents tracing / OpenAI Evals** | span attributes/events for resource-id + scenarioId; schema-backed eval records; deterministic vs model-graded split | GPT-5.5 `[gpt55/i2, i4]` |
   203	| **Large Language Monkeys (Brown et al.)** | coverage scales log-linear with sampling → repeated-sampling stabilizes D4 | MiniMax `[minimax/i1 F6]` `[SOURCE: arxiv.org/abs/2407.21787]` |
   204	
   205	---
   206	
   207	## 3. Recommended Lane C Design (Concrete, Decision-Ready)
   208	
   209	### 3.1 Scoring dimensions + weights
   210	
   211	```
   212	Weighted layer (0–100):
   213	  D1 Routing/Activation   25   → interSkill 12 (advisor) + intraSkill 13 (smart router)
   214	  D2 Unprompted Discovery 20   → Hit@k / Recall@k / MRR / cost-weighted precision
   215	  D4 Usefulness (ablation)25   → skill-on − skill-off; net value = benefit − context cost
   216	  D3 Efficiency           15   → calls/tokens to first expected resource; wasted loads
   217	Gate layer (caps verdict regardless of weighted score):
   218	  D5 Structural Connectivity 15 → dead keys, orphan refs, empty intent maps + contamination-lint
   219	Verdict band (calibrate on pilot): PASS ≥80 & no gate hit | CONDITIONAL 50–79 or gate | FAIL <50 or critical gate
   220	Repeatability → confidence modifier (report score ± variance), NOT a 6th score.
   221	```
   222	Weights are the reconciled cluster; **calibrate on a 2–3-skill pilot before trusting absolute thresholds** (unanimous open question). Normalize per-skill (baseline→delta), not cross-skill absolute.
   223	
   224	### 3.2 The five-stage funnel (scoring backbone + bottleneck localizer + remediation router, one structure)
   225	
   226	`1 Reachable (D5) → 2 Activated-inter (D1 advisor) → 3 Routed-intra (D1 router) → 4 Discovered-behavioral (D2) → 5 Useful-causal (D4)`. Per fixture record `firstFailingStage`; the aggregate funnel's **largest single-stage drop-off is the headline bottleneck** `[opus/i3 F4, opus/i4 F3]`.
   227	
   228	### 3.3 Hint-free dispatch/capture harness architecture
   229	
   230	```
   231	SCENARIO LOAD  fixture = { public{prompt,runtime,boundary,contract}, private{expectedSkill,
   232	               expectedIntentKeys,expectedResources[],negativeActivation,rubric} }
   233	   │  (private NEVER crosses dispatch boundary; key derived from skill's RESOURCE_MAP)
   234	CONTAMINATION GATE  linter (routers' own substring logic) rejects skill name/path/basename/
   235	   │  trigger/keyword/intent-label/command in public.prompt → FAIL = fixture bug, not skill
   236	DISPATCH  Mode A router-replay (deterministic, default/CI) ‖ Mode B live dispatch (periodic);
   237	   │  reuse dispatch-model.cjs across 5 executors; STRIP advisor/hook brief from subject;
   238	   │  capture advisor_recommend OUT-OF-BAND as D1 inter-skill signal
   239	TRACE PARSE  parse-resource-loads.cjs → {observed_resources[], tool_trace[]}; canonicalize
   240	   │  ALL file-touch verbs (Read + Bash cat/rg + Grep + Glob); set-membership not order
   241	SCORE (post-run join)  expectedResources × resource-loads.jsonl × routerTrace.json × outcome
   242	   │  → D1–D5; advisor 5-lane scorer reused (not re-implemented); k-run variance
   243	VALIDITY CONTROLS  hinted-vs-clean calibration arm | decoy-skill negative control | blind-to-rubric
   244	REPORT  report.json (machine) + report.md (rendered from json) + runQuality block
   245	```
   246	
   247	### 3.4 Scorer
   248	
   249	- **D1 interSkill** = `advisor_recommend` per fixture + reuse `advisor_validate` corpus/holdout `perSkill[]`; flag derived-dominant 0.72-cap and sub-0.05 ambiguity clusters. **D1 intraSkill** = router-replay loaded-set vs gold `RESOURCE_MAP[intent]` (deterministic, post-hoc from the AI's actual task text).
   250	- **D2** = Hit@k/Recall@k + cost-weighted precision over canonicalized loads; credit only existing inventory paths (reject hallucinated paths).
   251	- **D3** = calls/tokens to first expected resource + wasted-load count + fallback/dead-end counts.
   252	- **D4** = skill-on vs skill-off via Lane B's pluggable `--grader noop|mock|llm`; report quality delta + net value (benefit − context cost) + harm check.
   253	- **D5** = static pre-run: dead `RESOURCE_MAP` keys, orphan refs, empty intent maps, broken intra-skill links — **runs first and gates** the behavioral dimensions.
   254	
   255	### 3.5 Report format
   256	
   257	Dual artifact (`report.json` Lane-B-shaped + `report.md` deep-review-shaped, md from json). Sections: run header (with resolved skill root + metadata hash for rename invalidation) → corpus integrity → executive scorecard (composite ± confidence, D1–D5, hard-finding banner, 2×2 utilization matrix) → per-dimension drill-down → funnel rollup → **ranked bottlenecks** (each: id, severity P0/P1/P2, stage, finding-class, `file:locus`, evidence trace, likely cause, one-line remediation, `handoffLane`) → `runQuality` block → finding-disposition lifecycle → Planning-Trigger + Spec/Plan seeds (verbatim from deep-review) → artifacts manifest. Optional sidecar `routing-matrix-report.json` (cross-skill).
   258	
   259	### 3.6 Mapping to the three pluggable seams + loop-host mode
   260	

