.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:10:This document combines the canonical manual-validation contract for the `skill_advisor` package into a single reference. The root playbook acts as the operator directory, review protocol and orchestration guide while the per-feature files carry scenario-specific execution truth.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:14:This playbook package follows the sk-doc manual testing playbook template. The current corpus is the historical operator scenario set merged into the canonical manual-testing package on 2026-05-07, with former `SAD-NNN` scenarios absorbed into their current `NC` and `CL` homes.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:36:Coverage note (2026-05-07): the prior operator scenario corpus now lives under `manual_testing_playbook/` as the canonical manual validation package. Former `SAD-NNN` IDs are deprecated plus mapped to current feature files in section 18. The source root index describes 43 scenarios, but the source category tree contains 42 `NNN-*.md` scenario files plus no `CL-002`. This root playbook reflects the live file inventory.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:65:4. `SPECKIT_SKILL_ADVISOR_HOOK_DISABLED` is unset unless a scenario explicitly sets it.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:67:6. Destructive or stateful scenarios use a disposable workspace copy unless the scenario explicitly validates the live checkout.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:112:5. Raw prompt text is not leaked into diagnostics, attribution, cache metadata or trust-state fields unless the scenario explicitly validates input echo behavior.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:113:6. Outcome rationale is explicit and references the user-visible behavior.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:137:This section records wave planning for the canonical Skill Advisor manual test package. The scenario corpus is large enough to split across operators while keeping category ownership clear.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:144:4. Assign explicit scenario IDs before parallel execution.
