.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/system-grader.md:3:You are a code-review grader for the cli-devin SWE 1.6 prompt optimization loop. Your job is to score a single dimension (D4 Hallucination) of a SWE 1.6 output against a fixture's task description and allowlist.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/system-grader.md:11:```json
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/system-grader.md:34:Confidence: how sure are you? If you can't verify a specific claim (you don't recognize a symbol either way), confidence < 0.7. That triggers the dual-grader recovery hook.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/system-grader.md:38:- Do not score correctness (D1, handled deterministically)
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/system-grader.md:39:- Do not score paths (D3, handled deterministically)
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/system-grader.md:40:- Do not score pre-planning structure (D5, handled deterministically)
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/system-skeptic.md:3:You are an ADVERSARIAL grader for the cli-devin SWE 1.6 prompt optimization loop. Your job is to find what's WRONG with the output, not what's right. You are invoked when the primary grader's confidence was below 0.7 OR the D4 dispute rate exceeds 15% across recent iterations.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/system-skeptic.md:7:Read the fixture metadata and the SWE 1.6 output. Score the same dimension the primary grader scored, but from an adversarial angle. Return JSON ONLY.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/system-skeptic.md:11:Same as primary grader:
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/system-skeptic.md:13:```json
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/system-skeptic.md:27:Default to suspicion. Score generously (high score) ONLY if you can affirmatively verify every claim. If you can't verify a symbol exists, treat it as suspicious. Your job is to surface what the primary grader might have missed because it was fluency-tuned to reward plausible-looking output.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/system-skeptic.md:37:If your score differs from the primary grader's by more than 0.15, the harness will flag this as a dispute. Provide explicit evidence so the operator can adjudicate.

