.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:4:description: "Shared deep-loop runtime: executor + prompt-pack + validation + atomic state + coverage-graph + Bayesian scoring + fallback routing."
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:20:- executor configuration and audit metadata
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:21:- prompt-pack rendering
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:22:- post-dispatch validation
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:23:- atomic state files and JSONL repair
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:24:- loop locking and permissions gates
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:25:- Bayesian scoring and fallback routing
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:35:- A workflow needs Bayesian convergence scoring or fallback executor routing
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:42:- A package outside deep-review / deep-research needs deep-loop semantics (out of supported scope; open a packet to extend ownership)
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:49:This skill has no direct LLM-facing keyword triggers — it is invoked by workflow YAMLs (via `bash:` script calls) and by test imports. The router below documents which sub-domain to load for a given consumer query.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:56:  *"deep-loop runtime"*|*"deep-loop-runtime"*|*"executor config"*|*"prompt pack"*) DEEP_LOOP_INTENT=1 ;;
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:57:  *"coverage graph"*|*"deep_loop_graph"*|*"bayesian scorer"*|*"loop lock"*) DEEP_LOOP_INTENT=1 ;;
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:58:  *"fallback router"*|*"post-dispatch validate"*|*"jsonl repair"*) DEEP_LOOP_INTENT=1 ;;
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:77:lib/deep-loop/*.ts            # 10 runtime modules (executor, prompt-pack, validation, state, scoring, routing)
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:92:### Smart Router Pseudocode
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:95:IF request mentions a specific lib name (e.g. "bayesian-scorer", "prompt-pack"):
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:120:                    └─→ atomic-state, prompt-pack, post-dispatch-validate, etc.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:126:- `executor-config.ts` — schema + parsing for per-iteration executor settings
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:127:- `executor-audit.ts` — appends `executor` block to iteration JSONL (provenance)
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:128:- `prompt-pack.ts` — renders the iteration prompt template
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:129:- `post-dispatch-validate.ts` — validates iteration outputs (markdown + JSONL + delta)
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:130:- `atomic-state.ts` — atomic state-log writes
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:131:- `jsonl-repair.ts` — recovers corrupt JSONL state lines
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:132:- `loop-lock.ts` — single-writer locking
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:135:- `fallback-router.ts` — executor fallback decision matrix
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:144:The Runtime Boundary Decision (ADR-001) extends `deep-loop-runtime/lib/` with council-compatible infrastructure primitives while keeping operator-facing and domain workflow semantics in `deep-ai-council`. These primitives are consumed by downstream deep-ai-council orchestration (per-topic multi-round, session-findings registry, command and skill wiring, parity and cost docs) for per-topic orchestration, multi-topic session state, command wiring, parity tests and docs.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:147:- `multi-seat-dispatch.cjs` — runs seat executors in parallel for one council round, preserves seat result order, and returns fulfilled/rejected per-seat outcomes plus round summary counts.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:148:- `round-state-jsonl.cjs` — appends per-round JSONL records with a lock-file single-writer guard, repairs corrupt trailing JSONL before append, fsyncs writes, and exposes round-state readers for resume.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:149:- `adjudicator-verdict-scoring.cjs` — scores Round-N -> Round-N+1 adjudicator verdict deltas using ADR-003 weights for option change, confidence delta, material-risk Jaccard delta, axis flip rate, and blocking-disagreement delta.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:150:- `cost-guards.cjs` — normalizes and enforces ADR-004 defaults for `max_rounds_per_topic`, `max_topics_per_session`, `saturation_threshold`, and `seats_per_round`, including upper-bound seat-output calculation.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:151:- `session-state-hierarchy.cjs` — creates and validates the ADR-002 session -> topic -> round state shape, including stable `topic-NNN-slug` and `round-NNN` ids.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:153:The existing `lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts`, `lib/deep-loop/jsonl-repair.ts`, and `lib/deep-loop/loop-lock.ts` remain the sibling runtime contracts. Council modules mirror those durability semantics in a council-scoped CJS surface so downstream `deep-ai-council` phases can consume them without modifying deep-review or deep-research behavior.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:157:Four `.cjs` scripts replace the 4 deleted MCP tools, each honoring the same JSON-in / JSON-out contract documented in ADR-001 (the script interface contract):
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:165:| `scripts/fanout-pool.cjs` | n/a (new) | Concurrency-capped worker pool + status ledger for fan-out lineages | exports only (no main) |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:166:| `scripts/fanout-run.cjs` | n/a (new) | CLI lineage pool driver — spawns N headless CLI subprocesses (codex, claude, opencode, gemini, devin), each running the full loop in `lineages/{label}/`; salvage sweep via fanout-salvage.cjs after each subprocess exits | 0=all ok, 2=some failed, 3=all failed |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:167:| `scripts/fanout-salvage.cjs` | n/a (new) | Write-failure salvage: recovers missing iteration .md files from captured subprocess stdout; per-sessionId isolation preserved | exports only (no main) |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:168:| `scripts/fanout-merge.cjs` | n/a (new) | Cross-lineage merge: research (dedup by id + attribution) or review (strongest-restriction P0 rollup) → consolidated registry + fanout-attribution.md | 0=ok, 3=input |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:170:**Fan-out isolation invariant:** each CLI lineage receives its own `{base}/lineages/{label}/` artifact dir (via `config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir` override in `step_resolve_artifact_root`) and its own `session_id` for `convergence.cjs` + coverage-graph DB writes (PK includes session_id — no schema change, no collision). Same-kind replicas get distinct `SPECKIT_<KIND>_STATE_DIR` values to prevent lockfile contention.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:172:Each script: parses argv → opens `database/deep-loop-graph.sqlite` → calls the lib function → writes JSON to stdout → closes DB in `finally` → exits with the appropriate code.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:178:├── unit/         # 13 files — per-module unit tests (atomic-state, executor-config, etc.)
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:192:- **ALWAYS** open the SQLite DB inside a `try` block and close it in a `finally` block (script lifecycle invariant per ADR-001, the script interface contract)
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:193:- **ALWAYS** emit JSON-only output to stdout from `scripts/*.cjs` (workflow YAML parses stdout for output bindings)
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:196:- **ALWAYS** preserve atomic-state semantics when mutating JSONL state — never partial-write
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:197:- **ALWAYS** acquire `loop-lock` before any state-log mutation
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:202:- **NEVER** open the SQLite DB outside `lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts` — single owner of the connection
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:204:- **NEVER** write to `database/deep-loop-graph.sqlite` without holding the `loop-lock`
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:212:- **ESCALATE** if a script's stdout JSON contract changes — every workflow YAML output binding depends on the existing shape
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:231:- direct user command routing
