.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:126:| `lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts` | Appends an `executor` provenance block to each iteration JSONL | Post-hoc reviewers can tell which model and CLI produced each iteration without scraping the prompt |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:127:| `lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts` | Renders the iteration prompt template | The same prompt-template substitution code powers both loops, so changes propagate once |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:128:| `lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts` | Validates iteration outputs (markdown, JSONL, delta) | Catches malformed iteration writes before they corrupt state-log atomicity |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:134:Crash-resistant state writes for long-running autonomous loops.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:138:| `lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts` | Atomic state-log writes (tmpfile plus rename, never partial-write) |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:139:| `lib/deep-loop/jsonl-repair.ts` | Recovers corrupt trailing JSONL lines before append |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:140:| `lib/deep-loop/loop-lock.ts` | Single-writer lockfile around state mutations |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:147:Convergence detection plus fallback executor selection.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:152:| `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` | Executor fallback decision matrix when a primary executor times out or returns malformed output |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:174:| `lib/council/multi-seat-dispatch.cjs` | Runs seat executors in parallel for one council round, preserves seat order, returns fulfilled or rejected outcomes plus round summary counts |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:175:| `lib/council/round-state-jsonl.cjs` | Per-round JSONL records with lock-file single-writer guard, JSONL repair before append, fsync on write |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:176:| `lib/council/adjudicator-verdict-scoring.cjs` | Scores Round-N to Round-N+1 verdict deltas using ADR-003 weights (option change, confidence delta, material-risk Jaccard delta, axis flip rate, blocking-disagreement delta) |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:178:| `lib/council/session-state-hierarchy.cjs` | Creates and validates the ADR-002 session to topic to round state shape, with stable `topic-NNN-slug` and `round-NNN` ids |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:180:The council modules mirror the deep-loop durability contract (`atomic-state`, `jsonl-repair`, `loop-lock`) in a council-scoped CJS surface, so downstream `deep-ai-council` phases consume them without modifying deep-review or deep-research behavior.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:184:Four `.cjs` scripts replace the four deleted MCP tools. Each parses argv, opens SQLite inside a `try`, calls the relevant lib function, writes JSON to stdout, closes the DB in a `finally`, exits with the standardized code.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:193:Exit codes are uniform across all four: `0` ok, `1` script error, `2` DB error, `3` input validation error.
