.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:343:The SQLite database is missing, corrupt or locked by another writer. Check `database/deep-loop-graph.sqlite` exists and is writable. If the lockfile at `database/deep-loop-graph.lock` is stale (process holding it died without releasing), delete it after confirming no live writer exists (`ps aux | grep convergence.cjs`).
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:345:### Script exits with code 3 (input validation error)
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:351:The novelty signal is not dropping. Check `lib/deep-loop/bayesian-scorer.ts` for the active weight matrix. Possible causes: iteration outputs are corrupt and contribute fake novelty (`jsonl-repair.ts` should catch this), or the loop is genuinely surfacing new evidence and the hard cap at iter 10 is the correct stop.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:353:### Loop-lock acquisition times out
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:355:`DEEP_LOOP_LOCK_TIMEOUT_MS` default is 5 seconds. If a long-running upsert is in flight, raise the timeout. If a stale lock survived a crash, the lockfile at `database/<loop-type>.lock` may need manual removal after confirming no live writer.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:375:Not without a new ownership ADR. The ESCALATE clause in SKILL.md §4 routes a new consumer through a new ownership ADR so the runtime-to-consumer contract stays explicit.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:383:The Runtime Boundary Decision (ADR-001) decided that durability primitives (multi-seat dispatch, round-state JSONL, adjudicator scoring, cost guards, session-state hierarchy) belong with the other deep-loop durability primitives. Operator-facing and domain semantics stay in `deep-ai-council`. The split keeps `deep-ai-council` free to change its UX without touching durability contracts.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:387:Removed. The only retained test in the old location is `mcp_server/tests/deep-loop/review-depth-reducer.vitest.ts` because it tests `deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs`, which lives in the consumer skill rather than here.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:391:The SKILL.md is the operational contract loaded by AI agents at routing time (smart routing, rules, runtime architecture). This README is the human-facing introduction. The two are complementary, not duplicative. SKILL.md §1 redirects readers here for layout and history.
