.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.4.0.0.md:1:deep-loop-runtime now documents how to tell the runtime is healthy and where its consumers and tests live, closing two sk-doc conformance gaps without touching any runtime behavior.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.4.0.0.md:11:- **Added a SUCCESS CRITERIA section** -- the SKILL.md had no explicit health contract. It now lists the JSON stdout contract for every script entry point, consumer `lib/` import resolution, runtime SQLite and schema presence, and Vitest discovery. Consumer skills get a concrete "is the runtime working" checklist instead of inferring it.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.4.0.0.md:12:- **Added a REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES section** -- the references block pointed only at ADRs. It now also names the consumer skills (deep-review, deep-research), the cross-package Vitest config that discovers this skill's tests, and the changelog directory, so a reader can trace the runtime out to everything that depends on it.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:9:The v1.1.0.0 release-cleanup pass rewrote the README and fixed 4 surgical SKILL.md issues, but a 10-iteration cli-devin SWE-1.6 deep-research loop run on the v1.1.0.0 baseline surfaced 36 further findings the audit-and-validate phases missed. Three of the highest-impact findings were introduced or propagated by the v1.1.0.0 README rewrite itself: a fabricated `code-surface` node kind, a wrong cross-arc citation echoed into the changelog, and a 22-vs-27 vitest count drift. This taught a clear lesson: structural validation (template conformance) is not fact-checking (content accuracy). The deep-research loop is the fact-checker.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:23:All 17 feature_catalog descriptions verified against their source-module exported surface. Three drifted and were corrected (with matching playbook OVERVIEW lines): fallback-router (quota-pool framing), bayesian-scorer (computeScore + shouldDemote split), post-dispatch-validate (full validation surface). The other 14 were confirmed accurate. True population drift rate is 3/17 (18 percent), below the Phase-5 N=3 sample projection of 43 percent.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:31:Two new unit test files for the previously-uncovered `coverage-graph-query` (8 tests) and `coverage-graph-signals` (9 tests). Two weak council tests deepened: multi-seat-dispatch (2 to 6 tests) and round-state-jsonl (2 to 6 tests). All 29 tests pass via the system-spec-kit vitest harness.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:52:| `tests/council/{multi-seat-dispatch,round-state-jsonl}.vitest.ts` | deepened from 2 to 6 tests each |
