.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:2:title: "Fan-out CLI lineage driver"
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:3:description: "CLI lineage pool driver: TSX-bootstrapped entry point that spawns N headless CLI subprocesses (codex, claude, opencode, gemini, devin), each running the full loop in an isolated lineages/{label}/ sub-packet, with per-kind state-dir isolation and a post-subprocess salvage sweep."
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:6:# Fan-out CLI lineage driver
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:12:`fanout-run.cjs` bridges the pool primitive and the actual CLI executor subprocesses. It
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:13:parses the fanout config JSON, filters to CLI lineages (native lineages are handled by the
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:14:YAML `step_fanout_spawn_native` agent dispatch), creates `{base}/lineages/{label}/` and
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:15:`{label}/.executor-state/` directories per lineage, builds a "run the full loop" prompt,
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:18:`SPECKIT_FANOUT_LINEAGE_ID={label}` and `SPECKIT_<KIND>_STATE_DIR={stateDir}` environment
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:19:variables to prevent same-kind replica lockfile collisions, runs via `spawnSync` with a
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:20:generous timeout, saves subprocess stdout to `{lineageDir}/logs/fanout-lineage.out`, then
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:21:calls `runSalvageSweep` from `fanout-salvage.cjs`.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:25:Dispatches every CLI executor fan-out lineage. If this drifts, parallel research/review
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:26:runs can produce mis-isolated sub-packets, lose the per-kind state-dir isolation, or miss
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:34:`cli-gemini`, `cli-devin`. Per-lineage subprocess timeout = `min(iterations *
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:35:timeoutSeconds * 2, 4h)`. TSX bootstrap (mirrors `convergence.cjs` pattern) ensures
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:36:TypeScript imports (`parseFanoutConfig`, `expandLineages`) resolve in the CJS context. Exit
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:47:| `scripts/fanout-run.cjs` | Main entry: CLI arg parsing, per-kind command construction, pool orchestration, stdout capture, salvage call |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:48:| `scripts/fanout-salvage.cjs` | Called post-subprocess for write-failure recovery |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:49:| `scripts/fanout-pool.cjs` | `runCappedPool` for concurrency cap + ledger |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:50:| `lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts` | `parseFanoutConfig`, `expandLineages` imported via TSX |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:51:| `lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts` | `EXECUTOR_STATE_ENV_BY_KIND` constants for per-kind state dir naming |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:57:| `tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts` | 5 tests: native-only config returns early (no pool spawn), bad JSON config exits 3, missing required args exits 3, 2-lineage pool creates distinct dirs + ledger + summary, same-kind replica state dirs are distinct |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:65:- Catalog source: `feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md`
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/03-fanout-run.md:66:- Primary source files: `scripts/fanout-run.cjs`
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/08--council/05-session-state-hierarchy.md:2:title: "Session state hierarchy"
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/08--council/05-session-state-hierarchy.md:3:description: "Creates and validates the ADR-002 session->topic->round state shape, including stable topic-NNN-slug and round-NNN ids."
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/08--council/05-session-state-hierarchy.md:6:# Session state hierarchy
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/08--council/05-session-state-hierarchy.md:12:Creates and validates the ADR-002 session->topic->round state shape, including stable topic-NNN-slug and round-NNN ids.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/08--council/05-session-state-hierarchy.md:20:Three-level hierarchy: session contains N topics; each topic contains N rounds; each round contains N seat outputs. Topic ids use stable `topic-NNN-slug` form (3-digit numeric + dash + lowercase-kebab slug); round ids use `round-NNN`. Validator rejects malformed ids, duplicate slugs within a session, and out-of-order round numbering. Schema-conformant state hands off to round-state-jsonl for persistence.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/08--council/05-session-state-hierarchy.md:32:| `lib/council/session-state-hierarchy.cjs` | Runtime | 3-level session/topic/round state constructor + validator with stable ids. |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/08--council/05-session-state-hierarchy.md:38:| `tests/council/session-state-hierarchy.vitest.ts` | Test | Primary regression coverage for Session state hierarchy. |
