.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/02-fanout-pool.md:2:title: "Fan-out worker pool"
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/02-fanout-pool.md:3:description: "Concurrency-capped fan-out pool primitive: runCappedPool with injected worker, never-throws per-item settlement, ordered results, and JSONL status ledger."
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/02-fanout-pool.md:6:# Fan-out worker pool
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/02-fanout-pool.md:17:never sinks the pool. `appendStatusLedger` and `writeOrchestrationSummary` generalize the
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/02-fanout-pool.md:23:this pool without reimplementing the concurrency cap, settlement contract, or ledger shape.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/02-fanout-pool.md:29:Fully shipped in `fanout-pool.cjs`. Pure CJS (no TSX bootstrap), no CLI entry point, exports
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/02-fanout-pool.md:42:| `scripts/fanout-pool.cjs` | `runCappedPool`, `settleItem`, `buildPoolSummary`, `appendStatusLedger`, `writeOrchestrationSummary` |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/02-fanout-pool.md:48:| `tests/unit/fanout-pool.vitest.ts` | 10 tests: concurrency cap respected under gated workers, single-failure isolation, all-fail summary flag, ordered results, `onEvent` ledger emission, empty pool |
