.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/04-fanout-salvage.md:2:title: "Fan-out write-failure salvage"
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/04-fanout-salvage.md:3:description: "Post-subprocess salvage: recovers missing or empty iteration .md files from captured subprocess stdout (opencode --format json text parts or raw fallback), appending a salvaged_from_stdout event or writing a failed-marker placeholder."
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/04-fanout-salvage.md:6:# Fan-out write-failure salvage
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/04-fanout-salvage.md:12:After a CLI lineage subprocess exits, some executors (weak CLIs, sandboxed write
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/04-fanout-salvage.md:14:lineage state log to discover which iterations completed (`type == 'iteration'` records),
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/04-fanout-salvage.md:16:`extractTextFromOpencodeJson` on the saved stdout (concatenates opencode
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/04-fanout-salvage.md:17:`{type:"text",part:{text:...}}` JSONL lines; falls back to raw stdout ≥50 chars), writes the
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/04-fanout-salvage.md:18:recovered text and appends a `salvaged_from_stdout` JSONL event to the state log. When no
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/04-fanout-salvage.md:19:content is recoverable, writes a `fanout_salvage_failed` HTML comment placeholder.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/04-fanout-salvage.md:23:Proven mandatory from the packet-122 prototype: weak CLI executors intermittently fail to
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/04-fanout-salvage.md:24:write output files. Without salvage, those lineages contribute nothing to the final merge.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/04-fanout-salvage.md:30:Fully shipped in `fanout-salvage.cjs`. Pure CJS (no TSX bootstrap), exports only —
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/04-fanout-salvage.md:32:`require()`. `STATE_LOG_BY_LOOP_TYPE` maps `research` → `deep-research-state.jsonl` and
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/04-fanout-salvage.md:33:`review` → `deep-review-state.jsonl`.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/04-fanout-salvage.md:43:| `scripts/fanout-salvage.cjs` | `extractTextFromOpencodeJson`, `runSalvageSweep`, `STATE_LOG_BY_LOOP_TYPE` |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/09--fanout/04-fanout-salvage.md:49:| `tests/unit/fanout-salvage.vitest.ts` | 11 tests: `extractTextFromOpencodeJson` (5: null input, opencode JSON parts, raw fallback, too-short fallback, non-text JSON skipped); `runSalvageSweep` unit (5: no state log, all files present, salvage from opencode stdout, failed marker when no content, mixed present/missing); coverage-graph per-sessionId isolation (1) |
