.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/state_format.md:60:## 3. JSONL REPAIR
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/state_format.md:79:- Appends call repair before writing a new JSONL record.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/state_format.md:84:appendJsonlRecord(path: string, record: Record<string, unknown>): void
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/state_format.md:91:Source: `lib/deep-loop/loop-lock.ts`.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/state_format.md:104:Serialized lock file fields:
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/state_format.md:108:| `owner_pid` | `ownerPid` | Process id that owns the lock. |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/state_format.md:112:| `packet_id` | `packetId` | Spec-folder packet identifier the lock is scoped to. |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/state_format.md:113:| `runtime_kind` | `runtimeKind` | Executor kind that owns the lock (or `main` for orchestrator-held locks). |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/state_format.md:117:- Missing lock creates exclusive lock.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/state_format.md:120:- Race after write verifies current lock still belongs to owner.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/state_format.md:131:  stateLogPath: string;
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/state_format.md:134:  executorKind?: ExecutorKind;
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/state_format.md:144:The state log must include a canonical record whose `type === 'iteration'`. Variants such as `iteration_start` are not treated as the final iteration record for validation.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/state_format.md:146:Review-depth v2 validation is controlled by `DEEP_REVIEW_V2_ENFORCEMENT`.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/state_format.md:150:| `strict` | Hard-fail v2 validation failures. |
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/state_format.md:173:Source: `lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts`.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/state_format.md:175:When audited executor dispatch fails, the runtime can append a typed event to JSONL state. The event records iteration, executor kind, failure reason, exit status or signal when available, and provenance needed for later validation.
.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/state_format.md:177:The failure path uses `appendJsonlRecord` so corrupt trailing state is repaired before the dispatch failure is appended.
