.opencode/commands/deep/start-agent-improvement-loop.md:414:`/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` is one-session-only in the current release. Every invocation starts a fresh `new`-mode session with generation 1, writes a new journal, and evaluates candidates from iteration 1 for that session.
.opencode/commands/deep/start-agent-improvement-loop.md:416:Do **not** document or attempt journal replay, iteration carry-forward, or `resume`/`restart`/`fork`/`completed-continue` behavior here. Those lineage modes were described in earlier drafts but have no shipped runtime wiring; see `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md §Resume/Continuation Semantics (current release)` for the canonical retraction.
