+# Recommendations (build-ready)
+
+## Decision-record resolutions
+
+1. **Agent identity:** rename `@deep-agent-improvement` to `@deep-improvement`. File ids, TOML `name`, config keys, README listings, and mirror frontmatter should move in one changeset. Preserve the prose that this agent is proposal-only and Lane A-oriented; only the runtime identity broadens with the skill. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/003-skill-rename-deep-improvement/spec.md:48] [SOURCE: .codex/agents/deep-agent-improvement.toml:3]
+
+2. **`deep-model-benchmark` alias:** keep it. Treat it as a Lane B alias / command-route label, not the package name. Update advisor penalties and ownership links to point at `deep-improvement` where the target is the renamed package; keep `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop` and the alias group as stable user-facing entry points. Add Python parity for the alias if validation expects Python compatibility. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:33] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/explicit.ts:130] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:236]
+
+3. **Command verbs:** keep them. `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` still names Lane A accurately, and `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop` still names Lane B accurately. Only the `skill:` fields, hard-coded skill paths, and advisor/mirror ids change. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/spec.md:91] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/003-skill-rename-deep-improvement/spec.md:40]
+
+4. **Narrow vs wide:** execute NARROW. Explicitly record that `agent-improvement/` directories, command names, Lane A state filenames, and Lane A terminology remain as-is because they describe the lane, not the package. Wide rename is deferred because it would alter continuity and resume semantics. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/context-index.md:41] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/research.md:164]
+
+## Atomic rename runbook
+
+0. **Preflight freeze inventory.** Generate a four-column inventory: `file | class | action | verification`. Classes: `active-op`, `active-doc`, `generated`, `historical`. Denylist `*/specs/**/iterations/*`, `*/review/**`, `*/research/**`, `*/z_archive/**`, `*.raw.txt`, and completed historical packets unless a path is explicitly allowlisted. This prevents the rename from rewriting evidence history. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/research.md:168] [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/research.md:285]
+
+1. **Create a temporary compatibility bridge in advisor aliases.** Change the TS canonical group from `deep-agent-improvement` to `deep-improvement`, retaining `deep-agent-improvement`, `sk-deep-agent-improvement`, `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop`, and `command-spec-kit-deep-agent-improvement` as aliases until the final active census is clean. Mirror the same bridge in Python. If the alias system cannot represent package aliases safely, skip the bridge and do a hard cutover, but document the decision. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:52] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:263]
+
+2. **Move the canonical skill package.** Run `git mv .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement .opencode/skills/deep-improvement`. In the moved `SKILL.md`, update `name: deep-improvement`, description, triggers, keyword comment, and prose that names the package. Keep Lane A and Lane B tokens (`agent-improvement`, `model-benchmark`) where they refer to lane directories, commands, or state contracts. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:2] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:27] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:87]
+
+3. **Sweep self-references inside the moved skill.** Update active self-references in READMEs, feature catalog, manual playbooks, changelog entries that describe current behavior, and scripts with hard-coded package paths. Do not rename `assets/agent-improvement`, `references/agent-improvement`, `scripts/agent-improvement`, `agent-improvement-state.jsonl`, or Lane A command text. [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:135] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md:333] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/dispatch-model.cjs:151]
