# Focus

IQ7: convert the Phase 001 rename impact map into an ordered, atomic, reverse-safe execution runbook for `deep-agent-improvement -> deep-improvement`, and resolve the four decision-record forks that gate Phase 003:

- Agent identity: rename `@deep-agent-improvement` to `@deep-improvement`.
- `deep-model-benchmark` alias: keep as the Lane B alias and command-route label; remap any references that point at the renamed skill id.
- Command verbs: keep `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` and `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop`.
- Rename scope: execute the operator-selected NARROW scope now; leave the wider `agent-improvement` token-family rename to a separate packet if it is ever wanted.

# Actions Taken

- Read the converged Phase 001 research report, especially RQ6 and section 4, and re-anchored on its explicit safe-ordering and surface buckets. [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/122-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/001-skill-benchmark-deep-research/research/research.md:150]
